POLYWELL SELLING TWO-WAY OPTERON RACK SERVER ON WEB
(Source: IDG.net) Polywell Computers is selling a rack server
with dual Opteron processors from AMD, although the clock speed
of the new chips and the price of the server are still
undetermined.
http://www.idg.net/go.cgi?id=779526

VERISIGN CREATES NEW SUBSIDIARY FOR REGISTRAR BUSINESS
(Source: Computerworld) The company's domain registrar business,
including domain name sales, Web site and e-mail services, will
be run by its Network Solutions subsidiary.
http://www.idg.net/go.cgi?id=779527

NETWORK ASSOCIATES BAGS DEERSOFT
(Source: IDG.net) Network Associates started 2003 by putting spam
between the crosshairs. On Monday the company announced the
acquisition of Deersoft, a maker of antispam software, for an
undisclosed sum.
http://www.idg.net/go.cgi?id=779528

CISCO, IBM PAIR TO DELIVER FIBRE CHANNEL PRODUCTS
(Source: Network World Fusion) Cisco and IBM agreed to combine
the companies Fibre Channel storage-area networking products to
sell to customers.
http://www.idg.net/go.cgi?id=779529

PHILIPS, GENERAL ATOMIC TO WORK ON UWB CHIPS
(Source: IDG.net) A joint effort is aimed at producing chipsets
for wireless network equipment that runs more than 40 times as
fast as today's IEEE 802.11b networks.
http://www.idg.net/go.cgi?id=779530

MICROSOFT LAUNCHES U.S. SMARTPHONE PUSH
(Source: Computerworld) Microsoft and two hardware makers are
announcing mobile phones that run Microsoft's Smartphone software
and can be used on cellular networks in the U.S.
http://www.idg.net/go.cgi?id=779531

AMERICAN AIRLINES SECURES WIRELESS LANS IN DENVER
(Source: Computerworld) American Airlines has made sweeping
changes to improve wireless security. But public airport WLANs
are still a haven for hacker activity.
http://www.idg.net/go.cgi?id=779532


